posts.raw_content:
I was walking through the local Walmart and they have Walmart radio playing over the store sound system. 

They said that they are committed to America (total propaganda) and that anyone who's a small business owner or who manufactures products that are "shelf ready" to contact Walmart corporate to get their products in the stores.

After 30 years Walmart finally wants to stock American made products again. Obviously this is to avoid the tariffs which at this point aren't going away. But it's still an interesting change, and quite a positive one for the manufacturing belt. 

In the school supply section they had the Walmart brands pencils which were made in india, Ticonderoga which is Mexcio, China and India, but this year they had another small brand US made in Tennessee. 

It's actually happening, products are being made in the US again. Keep a sharp eye out when shopping and try to buy local when you see US products!
